<paragraph id="8BCA96356B2ACB5EFF35FA640DD5DC3A" blockId="7.[136,1452,1312,1915]" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFF35FA640F7DDEAF" box="[189,329,1420,1446]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Fungicolous</emphasis>
, growing on a fruiting body of 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B2ACB5EFD2FFA640D16DEAF" box="[679,802,1420,1446]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="7" pageNumber="35" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Boletaceae</taxonomicName>
sp. 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFCC6FA640A30DEAF" bold="true" box="[846,1028,1420,1446]" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Asexual morph</emphasis>
: Hyphomycetous. 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B2ACB5EFB5FFA640B7EDEAF" authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[1239,1354,1420,1446]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="7" pageNumber="37" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">Mycelium</taxonomicName>
forming a loosely attached layer on the fruiting body of the host (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFCAAFA580D85DEC3" box="[802,945,1456,1482]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2a</figureCitation>
). On PDA medium, colony forming a thick mat, white at the beginning, then becoming yellow (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFD6CFA3C0DA4DEE6" box="[740,912,1492,1519]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2b, c</figureCitation>
). 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B2ACB5EFC2FFA3C0A21DEE7" authorityName="Corda" authorityYear="1842" box="[935,1045,1492,1518]" class="Incertae sedis" family="Incertae sedis" genus="Mycelium" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Fungi" order="Incertae sedis" pageId="7" pageNumber="35" phylum="Incertae sedis" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFC2FFA3C0A21DEE7" box="[935,1045,1492,1518]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Mycelium</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
superficial, copious, developing as floccose masses of septate, branched, warted and hyaline hyphae bearing robust conidiophores with white spore masses (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFF07F9F40F2BDD3E" box="[143,287,1564,1591]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2b</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFEBDF9F40FEEDD3F" box="[309,474,1564,1590]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Conidiophores</emphasis>
hyaline, erect, flexuous, branched, septate, warted. With 
<specimenCount id="9D735DBC6B2ACB5EFBF8F9F50AEADD3E" box="[1136,1246,1565,1591]" pageId="7" pageNumber="35" type="generic" typeStatus="types">two types</specimenCount>
of 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFA80F9F40E8FDD53" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">conidiogenous cells</emphasis>
phialidic and aleuriogenic (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFE7AF9A80C84DD52" box="[498,688,1600,1627]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2d– f, i</figureCitation>
). 
<typeStatus id="54CE28976B2ACB5EFD4DF9A90CC9DD52" box="[709,765,1601,1627]" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Type</typeStatus>
A: 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFCAEF9A80DA4DD53" box="[806,912,1600,1626]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Phialides</emphasis>
in 2–3 verticels, hyaline, warted, 16–40 × 4–5.5 μm (x̅ = 25 × 5 μm, n = 30), attenuating to 1.5–3.0 μm at their apices (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFC2BF98C0A5EDD76" box="[931,1130,1636,1663]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2d, g, h</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFBF7F98C0B2ADD77" box="[1151,1310,1636,1662]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Phialoconidia</emphasis>
acrogenous, hyaline, ampulliform, aseptate, 12–18 × 5.5–7.5 μm (x̅ = 14.5 × 6.5 μm, n = 50) (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFC74F9600A99DDAA" box="[1020,1197,1672,1699]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2k–m</figureCitation>
). 
<typeStatus id="54CE28976B2ACB5EFB36F9610AC2DDAA" box="[1214,1270,1673,1699]" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Type</typeStatus>
B: 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFA93F9600B98DDAB" box="[1307,1452,1672,1698]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Aleuriogenic</emphasis>
discrete, on short side branches, hyaline, warted (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFD23F9440D54DDCE" box="[683,864,1708,1735]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2e, f, i</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFCFDF9440A29DDCF" box="[885,1053,1708,1734]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Aleurioconidia</emphasis>
hyaline at the beginning, becoming golden yellow when mature, subglobose to globose, thick 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFC9BF9380D28DDE3" bold="true" box="[787,796,1744,1770]" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">-</emphasis>
walled, aseptate, with angular tubercles on surface, 20–27 × 19–26 μm (x̅ = 23 × 22.5 μm, n = 50) (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFDFCF91C0D79DC06" box="[628,845,1780,1807]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2e, f, i, j</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFCEDF91C0DE5DC07" box="[869,977,1780,1806]" italics="true" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Tubercles</emphasis>
, cylindrical, 1–1.5 μm, often with apical depression, densely arranged (
<figureCitation id="134E8AB06B2ACB5EFE53F8F00C55DC3A" box="[475,609,1816,1843]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="8.[136,229,1563,1585]" captionTargetBox="[268,1315,199,1527]" captionTargetId="figure-19@8.[259,1327,190,1538]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. Hypomyces ampullaris (CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of Boletus sp. b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia.Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5316526" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5316526/files/figure.png" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">FIGURE 2j</figureCitation>
). 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B2ACB5EFDFEF8F00DEEDC3B" bold="true" box="[630,986,1816,1842]" pageId="7" pageNumber="35">Sexual morph: Undetermined</emphasis>
.
</paragraph>
