<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B25CB51FE8CF9F40FD5DD39" authorityName="Jing Z. Sun" authorityYear="2021" box="[260,481,1563,1585]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ampullaris">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FE8CF9F40FD5DD39" box="[260,481,1563,1585]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">Hypomyces ampullaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(CGMCC 3.20157). a Yellow colony on a fruiting body of 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B25CB51FBA9F9F30ABFDD39" box="[1057,1163,1563,1584]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" genus="Boletus" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="species" species="undetermined">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FBA9F9F30A5DDD39" box="[1057,1129,1563,1584]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">Boletus</emphasis>
sp.
</taxonomicName>
b, c Forward and reverse of a colony on PDA. d–g Conidiophores. h Phialides. i Aleurioconidia on short side branches. j Aleurioconidia. k–m Phialoconidia. Scale bars: d–g = 50 μm, h–i = 25 μm, j–m = 10 μm.
</paragraph>
</caption>
<paragraph id="8BCA96356B25CB51FF35F9400CDADC58" blockId="8.[136,1452,1703,1874]" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FF35F9400EC9DDC8" box="[189,253,1704,1729]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">Notes</emphasis>
:—The new species has grown on fruiting bodies of 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B25CB51FCB4F94F0D83DDC8" box="[828,951,1703,1729]" class="Agaricomycetes" family="Boletaceae" kingdom="Fungi" order="Boletales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Basidiomycota" rank="family">Boletaceae</taxonomicName>
sp. containing only the asexual state. Among the known Boleticolous species of 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B25CB51FD8BF9240CB0DDEC" box="[515,644,1740,1765]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FD8BF9240CB0DDEC" box="[515,644,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">Hypomyces</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B25CB51FD07F9240D1CDDEC" authorityName="Jing Z. Sun" authorityYear="2021" box="[655,808,1739,1766]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Hypomyces" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ampullaris">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FD07F9240C97DDEC" box="[655,675,1740,1765]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">H</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FD27F9230D1CDDEC" box="[687,808,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">ampullaris</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is morphologically similar to 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B25CB51FBE6F9230EEEDC03" authority="Damon" authorityName="Damon" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Sepedonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ampullosporum">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FBE6F9230B98DDEC" box="[1134,1452,1739,1765]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">Sepedonium ampullosporum</emphasis>
Damon
</taxonomicName>
in forming candelabrum like conidiophores and producing ampulliform conidia. But 
<taxonomicName id="4C75EDB66B25CB51FB19F9180B69DC00" box="[1169,1373,1775,1802]" class="Sordariomycetes" family="Hypocreaceae" genus="Sepedonium" kingdom="Fungi" order="Hypocreales" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" phylum="Ascomycota" rank="species" species="ampullosporum">
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FB19F9180AABDC03" box="[1169,1183,1776,1802]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FB25F9070B69DC00" box="[1197,1373,1775,1801]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">ampullosporum</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in having longer phialides (30–80 × 3.5 μm) and larger ampulloconidia (14–20 × 6–8 μm), and pigment discoloration of medium (
<bibRefCitation id="EFE4EBC46B25CB51FE99F8DF0F93DC5B" author="Damon, S. C." box="[273,423,1847,1874]" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" pagination="86 - 96" refId="ref6960" refString="Damon, S. C. (1952) Two noteworthy species of Sepedonium. Mycologia 44 (1): 86 - 96. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1952.12024172" type="journal article" year="1952">Damon 1952</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation id="EFE4EBC46B25CB51FE3AF8DF0C52DC58" author="Sahr, T. &amp; Ammer, H. &amp; Besl H. &amp; Fischer M." box="[434,614,1847,1873]" pageId="8" pageNumber="36" pagination="935 - 943" refId="ref8203" refString="Sahr, T., Ammer, H., Besl H. &amp; Fischer M. (1999) Infrageneric classification of the boleticolous genus Sepedonium: species delimitation and phylogenetic relationships. Mycologia 91 (6): 935 - 943. https: // doi. org / 10.1080 / 00275514.1999.12061104" type="journal article" year="1999">
Sahr 
<emphasis id="B9014A276B25CB51FE64F8D00C11DC58" box="[492,549,1847,1873]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="36">et al.</emphasis>
1999
</bibRefCitation>
, 
